One person was shot dead on Monday morning during a service delivery protest in Mooi River, KwaZulu-Natal. ALSO READ | Traffic restored on N3 by the Greytown Road bridge following protest action The residents were protesting over problems with their water and electricity supply. They closed the main entrance to the Bruntville area and it is alleged that they moved to the N3 where they threw stones at passing vehicles. KwaZulu-Natal spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala confirmed that one person was shot by unknown people. She said on Monday morning at about 3 am, Mooi River community members embarked on a protest where they blockaded the R62 and R103 with burning tyres and stones. “At 5.30 am police received a report that a 26-year-old man who was protesting has been shot by an unknown person on Greytown Road. The victim sustained a gunshot wound on the chest and was confirmed dead at the scene. “The motive for the killing is unknown. Police are monitoring the Mooi River area. Charges of murder and public violence were opened at the Mooi River Police Station for investigation,” she said.